<item>
            <title>[FRC-10] Limited thread safety on reference counts</title>
                <link>http://jira.fudgemsg.org/browse/FRC-10</link>
                <project id="10011" key="FRC">C Reference Implementation</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a situation where one thread is acting as a consumer (read operations) of messages created by another. E.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thread A creates a message.&lt;br/&gt;
Thread A calls &quot;retain&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Thread A passes message pointer to common storage&lt;br/&gt;
Thread A signals thread B (e.g. a semaphore)&lt;br/&gt;
Thread A calls &quot;release&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thread B (after being signalled by A), gets message pointer from common storage&lt;br/&gt;
Thread B reads fields from message&lt;br/&gt;
Thread B calls &quot;release&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Non-atomic increment and decrement of the reference count can cause a race condition and improper behaviour at the release point.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="10259">FRC-10</key>
            <summary>Limited thread safety on reference counts</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="http://jira.fudgemsg.org/images/icons/improvement.gif">Improvement</type>
                                <priority id="3" iconUrl="http://jira.fudgemsg.org/images/icons/priority_major.gif">Major</priority>
                    <status id="5" iconUrl="http://jira.fudgemsg.org/images/icons/status_resolved.gif">Resolved</status>
                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                <assignee username="andrew">Andrew Griffin</assignee>
                                <reporter username="andrew">Andrew Griffin</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Wed, 9 Jun 2010 20:44:32 +0100</created>
                <updated>Wed, 9 Jun 2010 23:02:35 +0100</updated>
                    <resolved>Wed, 9 Jun 2010 23:02:35 +0100</resolved>
                                                                    <due></due>
                    <votes>0</votes>
                        <watches>0</watches>
                        <comments>
                    <comment id="10251" author="andrew" created="Wed, 9 Jun 2010 23:02:35 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Code is in place at andrewgriffin/Fudge-C to support atomic operations on pointers on Visual Studio builds. It needs to be more generic, e.g. fall back to pthreads for all cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                </comments>
                    <attachments>
                </attachments>
            <subtasks>
        </subtasks>
